1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Who is the Governor?

The Governor is:

Constitutional head of the State
Representative of the President in the State

📌 Mentioned in Articles 153–167

Every state has a Governor.

📌 One person can be Governor of multiple states.

🔵 Appointment of Governor
Appointed by the President of India
Not elected directly
🔹 Qualifications

To become Governor:

Citizen of India
Minimum age: 35 years
🔴 Term of Office
Normally 5 years
Holds office during pleasure of President

📌 Can resign earlier or be removed.

🔹 Powers of Governor
1️⃣ Executive Powers
Appoints Chief Minister
Appoints ministers on CM advice
Appoints Advocate General
2️⃣ Legislative Powers
Summons state legislature
Gives assent to bills
Can reserve bill for President
3️⃣ Financial Powers
Money Bill introduced only with Governor’s recommendation
4️⃣ Judicial Powers
Can pardon certain punishments under state laws
🔹 Discretionary Powers

Governor can act without ministerial advice in certain situations:

Hung Assembly
Reserving bill for President
President’s Rule recommendation

📌 Very important for UPSC.

🔹 Governor vs President
Feature	President	Governor
Level	Union	State
Appointed by	Electoral College	President
Article	52	153
Real power with	PM	CM
🔹 Important Facts
Governor is nominal executive at state level
Real executive → Chief Minister
